Supreme Court — Appellate Term, July, 1899.

Before Freedman, P. J., MacLean and Leventritt, JJ.

The Brock’s Commercial Agency, Limited, Appellant, v. Henry W. Bean, Respondent.

Appeal from a judgment in favor of the defendant, rendered in the Municipal Court of the city of New York, sixth district, borough of Manhattan. D. M. Porter, for appellant; Henry W. Bean, for respondent. Judgment affirmed, with costs to the respondent. No opinion.
